#: ../../../customisation/index.md:1
msgid "Customisation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../customisation/index.md:3
msgid ""
"Furo supports customisation of the theme's overall look and feel (through "
"theme options) as well as a few per-page tweaks."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../customisation/index.md:5
msgid ""
"This section serves to guide the user with customising Furo-based "
"documentation. This page lists all the theme-specific customisations, as "
"provided by this theme. Other pages in this section provide guidance for "
"making specific customisations when using Sphinx with Furo."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../customisation/index.md:23
msgid "Theme options"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../customisation/index.md:25
msgid ""
"[`html_theme_options`][sphinx-html_theme_options] in `conf.py` is used for "
"customisations that affect the entire documentation. This is for stuff like "
"fonts and colors. While this theme inherits some options from the built-in "
"`basic` Sphinx theme, only the ones documented here are supported."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../customisation/index.md:29
msgid "`light_css_variables` / `dark_css_variables`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../customisation/index.md:36
msgid ""
"Support for dark mode involved replacing `css_variables` with "
"`light_css_variables` / `dark_css_variables`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../customisation/index.md:39
msgid ""
"Furo makes extensive use of [CSS variables][css-variables]. These can be "
"overridden by the user and are used for stylizing nearly all elements of the "
"documentation. {doc}`colors` contains important details of how these "
"variables are used."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../customisation/index.md:41
msgid ""
"Setting `*_css_variables` is the recommended mechanism to override Furo's "
"default values for these variables."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../customisation/index.md:43
msgid ""
"html_theme_options = {\n"
"    \"light_css_variables\": {\n"
"        \"color-brand-primary\": \"red\",\n"
"        \"color-brand-content\": \"#CC3333\",\n"
"        \"color-admonition-background\": \"orange\",\n"
"    },\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../customisation/index.md:54
msgid ""
"Typos in the `*_css_variables` dictionary are silently ignored, and do not "
"raise any errors or warnings. Double check that your spellings and values "
"are correct and valid."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../customisation/index.md:59
msgid "`sidebar_hide_name`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../customisation/index.md:65
msgid ""
"Controls whether you see the project's name in the sidebar of the "
"documentation. This is useful when you only want to show your "
"documentation's logo in the sidebar. The default is `False`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../customisation/index.md:67
msgid ""
"html_theme_options = {\n"
"    \"sidebar_hide_name\": True,\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../customisation/index.md:73
msgid "`navigation_with_keys`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../customisation/index.md:79
msgid ""
"Controls whether the user can navigate the documentation using the "
"keyboard’s left and right arrows. The default is `False`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../customisation/index.md:81
msgid ""
"html_theme_options = {\n"
"    \"navigation_with_keys\": True,\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../customisation/index.md:89
msgid "`top_of_page_button`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../customisation/index.md:96
msgid ""
"This will be removed after 2024-11-01. Use `top_of_page_buttons` instead."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../customisation/index.md:99
msgid ""
"Controls which button is shown on the top of the page. The only supported "
"values are `\"edit\"` (the default) and `None`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../customisation/index.md:101
msgid ""
"html_theme_options = {\n"
"    \"top_of_page_button\": \"edit\",\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../customisation/index.md:109
msgid "`top_of_page_buttons`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../customisation/index.md:115
msgid ""
"Controls which buttons are shown on the top of the page. This is a list "
"which can be empty or contain one-or-more of the following values:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../customisation/index.md:117
msgid "`\"edit\"`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../customisation/index.md:118
msgid "`\"view\"`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../customisation/index.md:120
msgid ""
"html_theme_options = {\n"
"    \"top_of_page_buttons\": [\"view\", \"edit\"],\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../customisation/index.md:126
msgid "`announcement`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../customisation/index.md:132
msgid ""
"Add a site-wide announcement, to the top of every page when set. See {doc}`./"
"announcement` for the details."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../customisation/index.md:134
msgid "`footer_icons`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../customisation/index.md:140
msgid ""
"Changes the icons presented in the site footer. See {doc}`./footer` for the "
"details."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../customisation/index.md:142
msgid "Page specific tweaks"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../customisation/index.md:144
msgid ""
"[File-Wide metadata][sphinx-file-wide-metadata] is used for per-page "
"customisation, primarily for controlling which UI elements are presented."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../customisation/index.md:146
msgid "`hide-toc`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../customisation/index.md:152
msgid ""
"The \"Contents\" sidebar is automatically hidden for any pages that don’t "
"have any inner headings. It is possible to hide it even when a page has "
"inner headings, by setting `hide-toc` at the page level. See {doc}`./toc` "
"for an example."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../customisation/index.md:154
msgid "Custom CSS files"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../customisation/index.md:156
msgid ""
"If you want more control than what is provided by the above theme options, "
"see {doc}`injecting`."
msgstr ""
